(Translated by Google) We were in New York just for November 2nd, the "dias de lo muertos", and we decided to celebrate it with a Mexican lunch. On the internet many call it one of the best Mexican restaurants in the city and I confess I have never been to Mexico, so I don't have a real yardstick but I can only tell you that it was definitely the best Mexican food eaten in my life. La Contenta is a tiny place with about fifteen seats decorated in full Mexican style (for the occasion it was just decorated for the feast of the dead) with a narrow but very traditional menu with Tortilla chips, guacamole and tacos all strictly homemade . We chose a grilled asada taco and one with crispy catfish fillet both served with rice and bean cream and washed down with two excellent Margaritas. All sensational, absolutely approved is recommended  (Original) Eravamo a New York proprio per il 2 novembre, il “dias de lo muertos”, e abbiamo deciso di festeggiarlo con un pranzo messicano. Su internet molti lo definiscono uno dei migliori ristoranti messicani della città e io confesso non sono mai stata in Messico, quindi non ho un vero e proprio metro di paragone ma posso solo dirvi che è stato sicuramente il miglior cibo messicano mangiato in vita mia. La Contenta è un locale minuscolo con una quindicina di posti a sedere arredato in pieno stile messicano (per l’occasione era proprio arredato a festa dei morti) con un menù ristretto ma molto tradizionale con Tortilla chip, guacamole è tacos tutti rigorosamente fatti in casa. Noi abbiamo scelto un taco di carne asada cotta alla brace e uno con filetto di pesce gatto croccante entrambi serviti con riso e crema di fagioli è annaffiati da due ottimi Margarita. Tutto strepitoso, assolutamente approvato è consigliato

Omg this is my favorite Mexican food right now. It’s kinda like local famous restaurant that doesn’t look fancy outside but the food taste is very fancy.  Honestly, I don’t know any other ones’ name but only know the Cheviche which looks like vegetables on taco. I HATE FISH and I LOVE it. The combination of the fish with the sour(little fermented maybe) taste is just so wonderful with the tomatoes and few other vegetables on the top. I first tried Cheviche in my life in New Orleans and that one was in a cold soup and this one isn’t but the sour flavor with the fish is still same. Very gooooood.  Other two meues have lots of cheese in it so you’ll need Cheviche with it later lol. What I did with my boyfriend was ordering 2 orders of Cheviche and those other two so that we have one piece of Cheviche as an appetizer and save one to eat with those cheesy menus later. I was very smart! If you wanna order all three menus, just show it to the waitress. They’re all nice.

The fish tacos had an ok taste, but were very soggy. The costilla tacos were dry, bland, and plain. This restaurant didn’t live up to its 4+ star rating that’s on Google. Although it was a very small restaurant, the Decor was nice inside.  They sat the four of us right by the kitchen and the light from the kitchen was glaring uncomfortably into my eyes and my friends eyes the entire dinner. Our table was also just a few feet away from both the bathroom and the kitchen which was pretty unsanitary.  The best part of the meal was the Chips and Quac, otherwise my rating would have been lower. However, the waitress tried to charge us $2 eventually for getting more chips which wasn’t right.  One of my friends actually got sick from the Chicken Tacos and Mojito she had and we believe it was a small case of food poisoning. Two other friends also had the Chicken Tacos and they didn’t really like them either.  I would not recommend this place for Mexican food and will not be going back.

Although my elusive quest for a go to Mexican restaurant in New York is ongoing, I can say that La Contenta is worth checking out.  The worst part about this place is waiting to get seated and the (lack of) reservation system; you can forget about coming here in a big group and may very well have to come right when it opens or be prepared to wait an hour or more.  However once seated the service is excellent and attentive, the cocktails are great, the food is respectable and the portions are generous (entrees can reasonably be shared between two people and the small plates could satisfy most, especially if combined with an appetize).  Some notes on some of the things I've had on the menu:  The chips and guac is a must, and comes with the chips arranged almost as a flower in the guacamole.  The soup is rich and delicious.  The bartender knows his craft.  The shortrib taco is terribly mediocre but the tempura fish taco is enjoyable.

I would definitely head back to this place for bite or two.
